  "prompt": "What are some good NGOs working in the field of children's education in India?",
  "response": "There are several reputable NGOs in India that focus on children's education and work to improve educational access and quality. Here are some notable organizations:\n\n1. **Pratham**: One of the largest NGOs in India, Pratham focuses on providing quality education to underprivileged children through innovative programs and collaborations with local governments.\n\n2. **Teach for India**: A part of the Teach For All network, this organization recruits and trains young leaders to teach in low-income schools, aiming to build a movement for educational equity.\n\n3. **Akanksha Foundation**: This organization runs schools and provides education to children from low-income communities, with a mission to empower them through quality education.\n\n4. **Door Step School**: Focused on providing education to children in slums and marginalized communities, Door Step School operates various programs, including mobile schools and after-school tutoring.\n\n5. **Smile Foundation**: This NGO works on several initiatives related to children's education, health, and livelihood, focusing on empowering underprivileged children through various educational programs.\n\n6. **Bachpan Bachao Andolan**: Founded by Nobel laureate Kailash Satyarthi, this organization works to combat child labor and advocate for children's right to education.\n\n7. **Child Rights and You (CRY)**: CRY works to ensure children's rights by addressing issues like education, health, and protection. They partner with various grassroots organizations to drive change.\n\n8. **Save the Children India**: Part of an international network, Save the Children focuses on ensuring that children have access to quality education and advocating for their rights.\n\n9. **Goonj**: While primarily known for its work in sustainable development and urban-rural bridging, Goonj also invests in educational initiatives, particularly through their \"Educational Initiative\" which aims to improve educational infrastructure in rural areas.\n\n10. **Vidya Foundation**: This organization aims to provide quality education to the underprivileged and has developed educational programs and support for children in need.\n\nThese organizations vary in their approaches, from formal education to informal learning and advocacy, but all have a common goal of improving educational opportunities for children across India.",
